Good traditional cantonese food. I'd recommend the pan fried noodles, fried rice, flat noodles. They customize for you if you request any modifications
Best dim sum place ever

They’re open again after 3+ months!  We love this place, it was our dimsum and dinner go to even with a 1/2 hour drive. Just got our first pick up meal, so excited for it.  I literally dream of the day we can have dimsum here again when they reopen.
Good foods

I’ve been here a few times from before it was renovated and after and we usually get dim sum here and have never gone here for dinner before with my family. The dim sum has a wide selection of dishes from the dishes every place has such as chicken feet and tripe and dumplings but they also offer other selections which I haven’t gotten yet. Needless to say, if you want somewhere for dim sum this place is pretty good. Nice staff but on weekends it’s very crowded early so if you want seats, get there early or expect to wait a while.
Really liked the place. Good dimsum place .

Had reservations for 7:30. Was seated by 8. Ordered dishes, and first one came out around 8:30. Next few dishes took another hour or so. Ended up cancelling the last dish.  If you're not used to this type of environment don't come here. You'll have a lot of people pushing you out of the way all the time. It's just expected here.  I'm not sure why this place is popular, in terms of food quality for the price they're mediocre. It's a lot of sauce. The actual cooked food is generally overcooked and dry.

Went there for King Crab.  It is delicious.  We had 3 courses out of one crab.  Steam legs, deep fried the body and fried rice with the shell. and we order few more things to go with it.  We have a very good time and food is excellent.
Great dim sum and food here.

Good service and very well made dishes.
Good food.  Dinner may be expensive.

This review is for their afternoon Dim Sum service only. Dinner kitchen staff is usually a completely different crew. That being said... there is a pretty good variety of Dim Sum available, I tried six dishes. How can ALL of them be BLAND!?! I lost interest in attempting to ordering anything further. Three stars is because the servers were attentive and quick. If you have a craving for Dim Sum and any will do, then this is an option. But you can most definitely do better.

This is a great dim sum place.  We went around 12:30pm on a Monday and it was packed!  We usually go to Choi Fook for dim sum but wanted to try this place out.  There is a lot of sea food (which we don’t eat) but several members of the staff spoke English and told all the ladies with the dim sum carts not to bring us sea food!  They made a point of showing us all the things we could eat.  We are way too much and paid $26.  Chicken feet were very good, the odd pig buns are secretly filled with pastry cream (and delicious) and the ribs were lovely.  We will definitely be back.

(Translated by Google) The place is convenient to the station, the food is delicious, and the price is not expensive. The only downside is that there are too many people, and they have to wait every time.  (Original) 地方方便近车站,出品很好吃,价钱不贵。唯一的缺点就是人太多,每次都要等位。

I came here for dim sum with my mother sometime back. The food was okay. It was a very long wait. They do not take reservations, also it is cash only. Please be aware.

This server was extremely rude. He should be fired for him and another server had the nerve to approach me and ask me if I was a boy or a girl. Then him and the other server started laughing and walked away.
+ tasty Cantonese food, reasonable prices. - often busy, suggest RSVP for dinner, street parking only. = Reliable spot to satisfy your Cantonese food cravings.

We came for dim sum and that's what we got. Some of their dishes were good and some you could tell weren't so fresh. For example we ordered  both beef and pork ribs with rice crepe. The rice crepe was cold and gummy. Did not taste good at all. But on the other hand we ordered the Walnut buns which were very good. Sadly service also could have been better. You really have to flag the waiters down. We wanted to put in an order for a platter and it took us awhile before anyone would come over.
Love the sweet spicy eggplant with tofu! Clean, bright, nice staff

Golden Bay is my favorite dim sum place, great food and top notch service. There's usually a 15-20 minute wait time for dim sum. The service here is quick and attentive- always filling the teapot! I absolutely love the people here!  Some things I recommend are shrimp dumplings, custard pig bao, salt & pepper squid and fish maw & crab meat soup, fried sardines, and walnut shrimp with broccoli. Their fried sardines have lots of eggs inside of them, which are super tasty.
